SIMPLE: multiply
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Multiply
<hw>Mul"ti*ply</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Multiplied</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Multiplying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>multiplier</ets>, L. <ets>multiplicare</ets>, fr.
<ets>multiplex</ets> manifold. See <er>Multitude</er>,
<er>Complex</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To increase in number; to make
more numerous; to add quantity to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Impunity will <qex>multiply</qex> motives to disobedience.</q>
<rj><qau>Ames.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>To add (any given number or
quantity) to itself a certain number of times; to find the product of by
multiplication; <as>thus 7 <ex>multiplied</ex> by 8 produces the number
56; to <ex>multiply</ex> two numbers</as>. See the Note under
<er>Multiplication</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To increase (the amount of gold or silver) by the
arts of alchemy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Multiplying gear</b></col> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <cd>gear
for increasing speed.</cd> -- <col><b>Multiplying lens</b></col>.
<fld>(Opt.)</fld> <cd>See under <er>Lens</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Multiply</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Multiply
<hw>Mul"ti*ply</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To become greater
in number; to become numerous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When men began to <qex>multiply</qex> on the face of the earth,
and daughters were born unto them.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. vi.
1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To increase in extent and influence; to
spread.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The word of God grew and <qex>multiplied</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Acts
xii. 24.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To increase amount of gold or silver by the arts of
alchemy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Multipolar</ent>⟦br⟧
